videos.description: Miami QB Malik Rosier is taken down in his own territory by Dewayne Hendrix for a loss of six in the first quarter.
videos.headline: Rosier sacked by Pitt early

videos.description: Quadree Henderson gets to the outside on the reverse run for a gain of 18 yards for the Panthers.
videos.headline: Pitt uses a reverse for a big gain

videos.description: Michael Pinckney jumps on the high snap from Pitt and earns the turnover chain on the sideline for the Hurricanes.
videos.headline: Miami recovers fumble from high snap

videos.description: Ahmmon Richards shows off his balance to stay in bounds on a 23-yard touchdown pass from Malik Rosier to put Miami in the lead.
videos.headline: Miami's Richards extends for the TD

videos.description: Miami's Sheldrick Redwine pops the ball from Chris Clark's grip and is recovered by Jaquan Johnson, who gives the turnover chain to Redwine.
videos.headline: Hurricanes force second turnover

videos.description: Pitt QB Kenny Pickett scrambles and leaps for a six-yard rushing touchdown to give the Panthers a 10-7 lead.
videos.headline: Pickett goes airborne for Pitt TD

videos.description: Miami head coach Mark Richt says his team needs to take advantage of the turnovers the defense is creating as they enter the half down 10-7 against Pitt.
videos.headline: Richt: 'Need to score off turnovers'

videos.description: Kenny Pickett takes a hit as he completes a big 29-yard pass to Jester Weah on third down for the Panthers.
videos.headline: Pitt's Pickett finds Weah for big play

videos.description: Kenny Pickett shovels the ball to Qadree Ollison, who dives in for a five-yard touchdown to put Pitt up over Miami 17-7.
videos.headline: Ollison takes shovel pass in for Pitt TD

videos.description: Coming in for Malik Rosier, Evan Shirreffs goes 3-and-out after this sack by Pittsburgh's Avonte Maddox in the fourth quarter.
videos.headline: Pitt sacks backup QB for Miami

videos.description: Kenny Pickett's pass is almost picked off as it tips off a defender's fingers as Quadree Henderson holds on for 19 yards.
videos.headline: Henderson catches tipped pass for Pitt

videos.description: Kenny Pickett takes it himself 22 yards on 4th down and dives for the pylon to put Pitt up 24-7 over Miami.
videos.headline: Pickett dives for huge Pitt TD

videos.description: Braxton Berrios gets Miami within ten on a 39-yard touchdown pass from Malik Rosier.
videos.headline: Berrios gets wide open for Miami TD

videos.description: Miami recovers an onside kick that ricochets off a Pitt player to give them a chance late in the 4th quarter.
videos.headline: Miami recovers onside kick

videos.description: Pitt head coach Pat Narduzzi says his 4-7 team will seal the deal and knock off No. 2 Miami.

tracking.trackingName: NCF One-Play (Pitt coach guarantees win at halftime) 2017/11/24

videos.headline: Pitt coach guarantees win at halftime

videos.description: Avonte Maddox knocks the ball loose from Malik Rosier as the ball is recovered by Dewayne Hendrix to give Pitt the win over Miami.
videos.headline: Pitt forces fumble to take down Miami

videos.description: Pitt head coach Pat Narduzzi called his team's comeback at halftime and says his team knew all week what they were capable of as his team takes down #2 Miami.
videos.headline: Narduzzi: 'Our guys believed all week'

videos.description: Miami head coach Mark Richt says he has no idea what is going to happen in the College Football Playoff picture.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Presser (Richt: 'no idea what's going to happen') 2017/11/24 ESHEET

videos.headline: Richt: 'no idea what's going to happen'

videos.description: The U was undefeated until they went to Pittsburgh, who are notorious for taking down ranked opponents.

videos.headline: Pitt's upset of No. 2 Miami is history repeated

videos.description: Bob Wischusen and Brock Huard discuss the implications for Miami's playoff chances after a stunning upset at Pittsburgh and the disappointing play of Miami QB Malik Rosier.
videos.headline: Miami's playoff chances aren't over yet
